@node "Abort Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Abort Intrinsic"
@next "Abs Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Abort Intrinsic
...............

     CALL Abort()

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Prints a message and potentially causes a core dump via @{b}abort(3)@{ub}.

@endnode

@node "Abs Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Abs Intrinsic"
@next "Access Intrinsic"
@prev "Abort Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Abs Intrinsic
.............

     Abs(A)

Abs: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}REAL@{ub} function.  The exact type depends on that of
argument A--if A is @{b}COMPLEX@{ub}, this function's type is @{b}REAL@{ub} with the same
@{b}KIND=@{ub} value as the type of A.  Otherwise, this function's type is the
same as that of A.

A: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}, @{b}REAL@{ub}, or @{b}COMPLEX@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns the absolute value of A.

   If A is type @{b}COMPLEX@{ub}, the absolute value is computed as:

     SQRT(REALPART(A)**2+IMAGPART(A)**2)

Otherwise, it is computed by negating A if it is negative, or returning
A.

   See @{"Sign Intrinsic" link "Sign Intrinsic"}, for how to explicitly compute the positive or
negative form of the absolute value of an expression.

@endnode

@node "Access Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Access Intrinsic"
@next "AChar Intrinsic"
@prev "Abs Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Access Intrinsic
................

     Access(NAME, MODE)

Access: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

NAME: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

MODE: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Checks file NAME for accessibility in the mode specified by MODE and
returns 0 if the file is accessible in that mode, otherwise an error
code if the file is inaccessible or MODE is invalid.  See @{b}access(2)@{ub}.  A
null character (@{b}CHAR(0)@{ub}) marks the end of the name in NAME--otherwise,
trailing blanks in NAME are ignored.  MODE may be a concatenation of
any of the following characters:

@{b}r@{ub}
     Read permission

@{b}w@{ub}
     Write permission

@{b}x@{ub}
     Execute permission

@{b}SPC@{ub}
     Existence

@endnode

@node "AChar Intrinsic" "g77.guide/AChar Intrinsic"
@next "ACos Intrinsic"
@prev "Access Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

AChar Intrinsic
...............

     AChar(I)

AChar: @{b}CHARACTER*1@{ub} function.

I: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}f2c@{ub}, @{b}f90@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns the ASCII character corresponding to the code specified by I.

   See @{"IAChar Intrinsic" link "IAChar Intrinsic"}, for the inverse of this function.

   See @{"Char Intrinsic" link "Char Intrinsic"}, for the function corresponding to the system's
native character set.

@endnode

@node "ACos Intrinsic" "g77.guide/ACos Intrinsic"
@next "AdjustL Intrinsic"
@prev "AChar Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

ACos Intrinsic
..............

     ACos(X)

ACos: @{b}REAL@{ub} function, the @{b}KIND=@{ub} value of the type being that of argument
X.

X: @{b}REAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns the arc-cosine (inverse cosine) of X in radians.

   See @{"Cos Intrinsic" link "Cos Intrinsic"}, for the inverse of this function.

@endnode

