@endnode

@node "AImag Intrinsic" "g77.guide/AImag Intrinsic"
@next "AInt Intrinsic"
@prev "AdjustR Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

AImag Intrinsic
...............

     AImag(Z)

AImag: @{b}REAL@{ub} function.  This intrinsic is valid when argument Z is
@{b}COMPLEX(KIND=1)@{ub}.  When Z is any other @{b}COMPLEX@{ub} type, this intrinsic is
valid only when used as the argument to @{b}REAL()@{ub}, as explained below.

Z: @{b}COMPLEX@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns the (possibly converted) imaginary part of Z.

   Use of @{b}AIMAG()@{ub} with an argument of a type other than @{b}COMPLEX(KIND=1)@{ub}
is restricted to the following case:

     REAL(AIMAG(Z))

This expression converts the imaginary part of Z to @{b}REAL(KIND=1)@{ub}.

   See @{"REAL() and AIMAG() of Complex" link "REAL() and AIMAG() of Complex"}, for more information.

@endnode

@node "AInt Intrinsic" "g77.guide/AInt Intrinsic"
@next "Alarm Intrinsic"
@prev "AImag Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

AInt Intrinsic
..............

     AInt(A)

AInt: @{b}REAL@{ub} function, the @{b}KIND=@{ub} value of the type being that of argument
A.

A: @{b}REAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns A with the fractional portion of its magnitude truncated and
its sign preserved.  (Also called "truncation towards zero".)

   See @{"ANInt Intrinsic" link "ANInt Intrinsic"}, for how to round to nearest whole number.

   See @{"Int Intrinsic" link "Int Intrinsic"}, for how to truncate and then convert number to
@{b}INTEGER@{ub}.

@endnode

@node "Alarm Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Alarm Intrinsic"
@next "All Intrinsic"
@prev "AInt Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Alarm Intrinsic
...............

     CALL Alarm(SECONDS, HANDLER, STATUS)

SECONDS: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

HANDLER: Signal handler (@{b}INTEGER FUNCTION@{ub} or @{b}SUBROUTINE@{ub}) or
dummy/global @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} scalar.

STATUS: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub}; OPTIONAL; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Causes external subroutine HANDLER to be executed after a delay of
SECONDS seconds by using @{b}alarm(1)@{ub} to set up a signal and @{b}signal(2)@{ub} to
catch it.  If STATUS is supplied, it will be returned with the number
of seconds remaining until any previously scheduled alarm was due to be
delivered, or zero if there was no previously scheduled alarm.  See
@{"Signal Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "Signal Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

