@node "ANInt Intrinsic" "g77.guide/ANInt Intrinsic"
@next "Any Intrinsic"
@prev "And Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

ANInt Intrinsic
...............

     ANInt(A)

ANInt: @{b}REAL@{ub} function, the @{b}KIND=@{ub} value of the type being that of
argument A.

A: @{b}REAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns A with the fractional portion of its magnitude eliminated by
rounding to the nearest whole number and with its sign preserved.

   A fractional portion exactly equal to @{b}.5@{ub} is rounded to the whole
number that is larger in magnitude.  (Also called "Fortran round".)

   See @{"AInt Intrinsic" link "AInt Intrinsic"}, for how to truncate to whole number.

   See @{"NInt Intrinsic" link "NInt Intrinsic"}, for how to round and then convert number to
@{b}INTEGER@{ub}.

@endnode

