@node "Bit_Size Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Bit_Size Intrinsic"
@next "BTest Intrinsic"
@prev "BesYN Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Bit_Size Intrinsic
..................

     Bit_Size(I)

Bit_Size: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} function, the @{b}KIND=@{ub} value of the type being that of
argument I.

I: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar.

Intrinsic groups: @{b}f90@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns the number of bits (integer precision plus sign bit)
represented by the type for I.

   See @{"BTest Intrinsic" link "BTest Intrinsic"}, for how to test the value of a bit in a
variable or array.

   See @{"IBSet Intrinsic" link "IBSet Intrinsic"}, for how to set a bit in a variable to 1.

   See @{"IBClr Intrinsic" link "IBClr Intrinsic"}, for how to set a bit in a variable to 0.

@endnode

@node "BTest Intrinsic" "g77.guide/BTest Intrinsic"
@next "CAbs Intrinsic"
@prev "Bit_Size Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

BTest Intrinsic
...............

     BTest(I, POS)

BTest: @{b}LOGICAL(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

I: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

POS: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}mil@{ub}, @{b}f90@{ub}, @{b}vxt@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns @{b}.TRUE.@{ub} if bit POS in I is 1, @{b}.FALSE.@{ub} otherwise.

   (Bit 0 is the low-order (rightmost) bit, adding the value 2**0, or 1,
to the number if set to 1; bit 1 is the next-higher-order bit, adding
2**1, or 2; bit 2 adds 2**2, or 4; and so on.)

   See @{"Bit_Size Intrinsic" link "Bit_Size Intrinsic"}, for how to obtain the number of bits in a
type.  The leftmost bit of I is @{b}BIT_SIZE(I-1)@{ub}.

@endnode

