Cos Intrinsic
.............

     Cos(X)

Cos: @{b}REAL@{ub} or @{b}COMPLEX@{ub} function, the exact type being that of argument X.

X: @{b}REAL@{ub} or @{b}COMPLEX@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns the cosine of X, an angle measured in radians.

   See @{"ACos Intrinsic" link "ACos Intrinsic"}, for the inverse of this function.

@endnode

@node "CosH Intrinsic" "g77.guide/CosH Intrinsic"
@next "Count Intrinsic"
