@node "CTime Intrinsic (subroutine)" "g77.guide/CTime Intrinsic (subroutine)"
@next "CTime Intrinsic (function)"
@prev "CSqRt Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

CTime Intrinsic (subroutine)
............................

     CALL CTime(STIME, RESULT)

STIME: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

RESULT: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Converts STIME, a system time value, such as returned by @{b}TIME8()@{ub}, to
a string of the form @{b}Sat Aug 19 18:13:14 1995@{ub}, and returns that string
in RESULT.

   See @{"Time8 Intrinsic" link "Time8 Intrinsic"}.

   Some non-GNU implementations of Fortran provide this intrinsic as
only a function, not as a subroutine.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"CTime Intrinsic (function)" link "CTime Intrinsic (function)"}.

@endnode

@node "CTime Intrinsic (function)" "g77.guide/CTime Intrinsic (function)"
@next "DAbs Intrinsic"
@prev "CTime Intrinsic (subroutine)"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

CTime Intrinsic (function)
..........................

     CTime(STIME)

CTime: @{b}CHARACTER*(*)@{ub} function.

STIME: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Converts STIME, a system time value, such as returned by @{b}TIME8()@{ub}, to
a string of the form @{b}Sat Aug 19 18:13:14 1995@{ub}, and returns that string
as the function value.

   See @{"Time8 Intrinsic" link "Time8 Intrinsic"}.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"CTime Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "CTime Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

