@node "Dble Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Dble Intrinsic"
@next "DCos Intrinsic"
@prev "DbesYN Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Dble Intrinsic
..............

     Dble(A)

Dble: @{b}REAL(KIND=2)@{ub} function.

A: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}, @{b}REAL@{ub}, or @{b}COMPLEX@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns A converted to double precision (@{b}REAL(KIND=2)@{ub}).  If A is
@{b}COMPLEX@{ub}, the real part of A is used for the conversion and the
imaginary part disregarded.

   See @{"Sngl Intrinsic" link "Sngl Intrinsic"}, for the function that converts to single
precision.

   See @{"Int Intrinsic" link "Int Intrinsic"}, for the function that converts to @{b}INTEGER@{ub}.

   See @{"Complex Intrinsic" link "Complex Intrinsic"}, for the function that converts to @{b}COMPLEX@{ub}.

@endnode

