@next "DInt Intrinsic"
@prev "Digits Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

DiM Intrinsic
.............

     DiM(X, Y)

DiM: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}REAL@{ub} function, the exact type being the result of
cross-promoting the types of all the arguments.

X: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}REAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Y: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}REAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns @{b}X-Y@{ub} if X is greater than Y; otherwise returns zero.

@endnode

