@node "MClock Intrinsic" "g77.guide/MClock Intrinsic"
@next "MClock8 Intrinsic"
@prev "MaxVal Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

MClock Intrinsic
................

     MClock()

MClock: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns the number of clock ticks since the start of the process.
Supported on systems with @{b}clock(3)@{ub} (q.v.).

   This intrinsic is not fully portable, such as to systems with 32-bit
@{b}INTEGER@{ub} types but supporting times wider than 32 bits.  Therefore, the
values returned by this intrinsic might be, or become, negative, or
numerically less than previous values, during a single run of the
compiled program.

   See @{"MClock8 Intrinsic" link "MClock8 Intrinsic"}, for information on a similar intrinsic that
might be portable to more GNU Fortran implementations, though to fewer
Fortran compilers.

   If the system does not support @{b}clock(3)@{ub}, -1 is returned.

@endnode

@node "MClock8 Intrinsic" "g77.guide/MClock8 Intrinsic"
@next "Merge Intrinsic"
@prev "MClock Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

MClock8 Intrinsic
.................

     MClock8()

MClock8: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=2)@{ub} function.

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns the number of clock ticks since the start of the process.
Supported on systems with @{b}clock(3)@{ub} (q.v.).

   @{i}Warning:@{ui} this intrinsic does not increase the range of the timing
values over that returned by @{b}clock(3)@{ub}.  On a system with a 32-bit
@{b}clock(3)@{ub}, @{b}MCLOCK8@{ub} will return a 32-bit value, even though converted to
an @{b}INTEGER(KIND=2)@{ub} value.  That means overflows of the 32-bit value can
still occur.  Therefore, the values returned by this intrinsic might
be, or become, negative, or numerically less than previous values,
during a single run of the compiled program.

   No Fortran implementations other than GNU Fortran are known to
support this intrinsic at the time of this writing.  See
@{"MClock Intrinsic" link "MClock Intrinsic"}, for information on a similar intrinsic that might
be portable to more Fortran compilers, though to fewer GNU Fortran
implementations.

   If the system does not support @{b}clock(3)@{ub}, -1 is returned.

@endnode

