@node "Mod Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Mod Intrinsic"
@next "Modulo Intrinsic"
@prev "MinVal Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Mod Intrinsic
.............

     Mod(A, P)

Mod: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}REAL@{ub} function, the exact type being the result of
cross-promoting the types of all the arguments.

A: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}REAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

P: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}REAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns remainder calculated as:

     A - (INT(A / P) * P)

   P must not be zero.

@endnode

