@endnode

@node "NInt Intrinsic" "g77.guide/NInt Intrinsic"
@next "Not Intrinsic"
@prev "Nearest Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

NInt Intrinsic
..............

     NInt(A)

NInt: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

A: @{b}REAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: (standard FORTRAN 77).

Description:

   Returns A with the fractional portion of its magnitude eliminated by
rounding to the nearest whole number and with its sign preserved,
converted to type @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub}.

   If A is type @{b}COMPLEX@{ub}, its real part is rounded and converted.

   A fractional portion exactly equal to @{b}.5@{ub} is rounded to the whole
number that is larger in magnitude.  (Also called "Fortran round".)

   See @{"Int Intrinsic" link "Int Intrinsic"}, for how to convert, truncate to whole number.

   See @{"ANInt Intrinsic" link "ANInt Intrinsic"}, for how to round to nearest whole number
without converting.

@endnode

@node "Not Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Not Intrinsic"
@next "Or Intrinsic"
@prev "NInt Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Not Intrinsic
.............

     Not(I)

Not: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} function, the @{b}KIND=@{ub} value of the type being that of
argument I.

I: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}mil@{ub}, @{b}f90@{ub}, @{b}vxt@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns value resulting from boolean NOT of each bit in I.

@endnode

@node "Or Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Or Intrinsic"
@next "Pack Intrinsic"
@prev "Not Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Or Intrinsic
............

     Or(I, J)

Or: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}LOGICAL@{ub} function, the exact type being the result of
cross-promoting the types of all the arguments.

I: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}LOGICAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

J: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}LOGICAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}f2c@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns value resulting from boolean OR of pair of bits in each of I
and J.

@endnode

