PError Intrinsic
................

     CALL PError(STRING)

STRING: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Prints (on the C @{b}stderr@{ub} stream) a newline-terminated error message
corresponding to the last system error.  This is prefixed by STRING, a
colon and a space.  See @{b}perror(3)@{ub}.

