@node "TtyNam Intrinsic (subroutine)" "g77.guide/TtyNam Intrinsic (subroutine)"
@next "TtyNam Intrinsic (function)"
@prev "Trim Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

TtyNam Intrinsic (subroutine)
.............................

     CALL TtyNam(UNIT, NAME)

UNIT: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

NAME: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Sets NAME to the name of the terminal device open on logical unit
UNIT or to a blank string if UNIT is not connected to a terminal.

   Some non-GNU implementations of Fortran provide this intrinsic as
only a function, not as a subroutine.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"TtyNam Intrinsic (function)" link "TtyNam Intrinsic (function)"}.

@endnode

@node "TtyNam Intrinsic (function)" "g77.guide/TtyNam Intrinsic (function)"
@next "UBound Intrinsic"
@prev "TtyNam Intrinsic (subroutine)"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

TtyNam Intrinsic (function)
...........................

     TtyNam(UNIT)

TtyNam: @{b}CHARACTER*(*)@{ub} function.

UNIT: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns the name of the terminal device open on logical unit UNIT or
a blank string if UNIT is not connected to a terminal.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"TtyNam Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "TtyNam Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

