@next "Unlink Intrinsic (subroutine)"
@prev "UBound Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

UMask Intrinsic (subroutine)
............................

     CALL UMask(MASK, OLD)

MASK: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

OLD: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub}; OPTIONAL; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Sets the file creation mask to MASK and returns the old value in
argument OLD if it is supplied.  See @{b}umask(2)@{ub}.

   Some non-GNU implementations of Fortran provide this intrinsic as
only a function, not as a subroutine.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"UMask Intrinsic (function)" link "UMask Intrinsic (function)"}.

@endnode

@node "Unlink Intrinsic (subroutine)" "g77.guide/Unlink Intrinsic (subroutine)"
@next "Unpack Intrinsic"
@prev "UMask Intrinsic (subroutine)"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Unlink Intrinsic (subroutine)
.............................

     CALL Unlink(FILE, STATUS)

FILE: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

STATUS: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub}; OPTIONAL; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}unix@{ub}.

Description:

   Unlink the file FILE.  A null character (@{b}CHAR(0)@{ub}) marks the end of
the name in FILE--otherwise, trailing blanks in FILE are ignored.  If
the STATUS argument is supplied, it contains 0 on success or a nonzero
error code upon return.  See @{b}unlink(2)@{ub}.

   Some non-GNU implementations of Fortran provide this intrinsic as
only a function, not as a subroutine, or do not support the (optional)
STATUS argument.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"Unlink Intrinsic (function)" link "Unlink Intrinsic (function)"}.

@endnode

