Unpack Intrinsic
................

This intrinsic is not yet implemented.  The name is, however, reserved
as an intrinsic.  Use @{b}EXTERNAL Unpack@{ub} to use this name for an external
procedure.

@endnode

@node "Verify Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Verify Intrinsic"
@next "XOr Intrinsic"
@prev "Unpack Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

Verify Intrinsic
................

This intrinsic is not yet implemented.  The name is, however, reserved
as an intrinsic.  Use @{b}EXTERNAL Verify@{ub} to use this name for an external
procedure.

@endnode

@node "XOr Intrinsic" "g77.guide/XOr Intrinsic"
@next "ZAbs Intrinsic"
@prev "Verify Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

XOr Intrinsic
.............

     XOr(I, J)

XOr: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}LOGICAL@{ub} function, the exact type being the result of
cross-promoting the types of all the arguments.

I: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}LOGICAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

J: @{b}INTEGER@{ub} or @{b}LOGICAL@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}f2c@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns value resulting from boolean exclusive-OR of pair of bits in
each of I and J.

@endnode

@node "ZAbs Intrinsic" "g77.guide/ZAbs Intrinsic"
@next "ZCos Intrinsic"
@prev "XOr Intrinsic"
@toc "Table of Intrinsic Functions"

ZAbs Intrinsic
..............

     ZAbs(A)

ZAbs: @{b}REAL(KIND=2)@{ub} function.

A: @{b}COMPLEX(KIND=2)@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}f2c@{ub}.

Description:

   Archaic form of @{b}ABS()@{ub} that is specific to one type for A.  See
@{"Abs Intrinsic" link "Abs Intrinsic"}.

@endnode

