@node "Date Intrinsic" "g77.guide/Date Intrinsic"
@next "DbleQ Intrinsic"
@prev "DATanD Intrinsic"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

Date Intrinsic
..............

     CALL Date(DATE)

DATE: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}vxt@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns DATE in the form @{b}DD-MMM-YY@{ub}, representing the numeric day of
the month DD, a three-character abbreviation of the month name MMM and
the last two digits of the year YY, e.g. @{b}25-Nov-96@{ub}.

   This intrinsic is not recommended, due to the year 2000 approaching.
Therefore, programs making use of this intrinsic might not be Year 2000
(Y2K) compliant.  See @{"CTime Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "CTime Intrinsic (subroutine)"}, for information on
obtaining more digits for the current (or any) date.

@endnode

