@node "DTime Intrinsic (function)" "g77.guide/DTime Intrinsic (function)"
@next "FGet Intrinsic (function)"
@prev "DTanD Intrinsic"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

DTime Intrinsic (function)
..........................

     DTime(TARRAY)

DTime: @{b}REAL(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

TARRAY: @{b}REAL(KIND=1)@{ub}; DIMENSION(2); INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}badu77@{ub}.

Description:

   Initially, return the number of seconds of runtime since the start
of the process's execution as the function value, and the user and
system components of this in @{b}TARRAY(1)@{ub} and @{b}TARRAY(2)@{ub} respectively.  The
functions' value is equal to @{b}TARRAY(1) + TARRAY(2)@{ub}.

   Subsequent invocations of @{b}DTIME()@{ub} return values accumulated since the
previous invocation.

   On some systems, the underlying timings are represented using types
with sufficiently small limits that overflows (wraparounds) are
possible, such as 32-bit types.  Therefore, the values returned by this
intrinsic might be, or become, negative, or numerically less than
previous values, during a single run of the compiled program.

   Due to the side effects performed by this intrinsic, the function
form is not recommended.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"DTime Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "DTime Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

@node "FGet Intrinsic (function)" "g77.guide/FGet Intrinsic (function)"
@next "FGetC Intrinsic (function)"
@prev "DTime Intrinsic (function)"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

FGet Intrinsic (function)
.........................

     FGet(C)

FGet: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

C: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}badu77@{ub}.

Description:

   Reads a single character into C in stream mode from unit 5
(by-passing normal formatted input) using @{b}getc(3)@{ub}.  Returns 0 on
success, -1 on end-of-file, and the error code from @{b}ferror(3)@{ub} otherwise.

   Stream I/O should not be mixed with normal record-oriented
(formatted or unformatted) I/O on the same unit; the results are
unpredictable.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"FGet Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "FGet Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

@node "FGetC Intrinsic (function)" "g77.guide/FGetC Intrinsic (function)"
@next "FloatI Intrinsic"
@prev "FGet Intrinsic (function)"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

FGetC Intrinsic (function)
..........................

     FGetC(UNIT, C)

FGetC: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

UNIT: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

C: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}badu77@{ub}.

Description:

   Reads a single character into C in stream mode from unit UNIT
(by-passing normal formatted output) using @{b}getc(3)@{ub}.  Returns 0 on
success, -1 on end-of-file, and the error code from @{b}ferror(3)@{ub} otherwise.

   Stream I/O should not be mixed with normal record-oriented
(formatted or unformatted) I/O on the same unit; the results are
unpredictable.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"FGetC Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "FGetC Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

