@next "FPutC Intrinsic (function)"
@prev "FloatJ Intrinsic"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

FPut Intrinsic (function)
.........................

     FPut(C)

FPut: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

C: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}badu77@{ub}.

Description:

   Writes the single character C in stream mode to unit 6 (by-passing
normal formatted output) using @{b}getc(3)@{ub}.  Returns 0 on success, the
error code from @{b}ferror(3)@{ub} otherwise.

   Stream I/O should not be mixed with normal record-oriented
(formatted or unformatted) I/O on the same unit; the results are
unpredictable.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"FPut Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "FPut Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

@node "FPutC Intrinsic (function)" "g77.guide/FPutC Intrinsic (function)"
@next "IDate Intrinsic (VXT)"
@prev "FPut Intrinsic (function)"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

FPutC Intrinsic (function)
..........................

     FPutC(UNIT, C)

FPutC: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

UNIT: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

C: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}badu77@{ub}.

Description:

   Writes the single character C in stream mode to unit UNIT
(by-passing normal formatted output) using @{b}putc(3)@{ub}.  Returns 0 on
success, the error code from @{b}ferror(3)@{ub} otherwise.

   Stream I/O should not be mixed with normal record-oriented
(formatted or unformatted) I/O on the same unit; the results are
unpredictable.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"FPutC Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "FPutC Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

@node "IDate Intrinsic (VXT)" "g77.guide/IDate Intrinsic (VXT)"
@next "IIAbs Intrinsic"
@prev "FPutC Intrinsic (function)"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

IDate Intrinsic (VXT)
.....................

     CALL IDate(M, D, Y)

M: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

D: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Y: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(OUT).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}vxt@{ub}.

Description:

   Returns the numerical values of the current local time.  The month
(in the range 1-12) is returned in M, the day (in the range 1-31) in D,
and the year in Y (in the range 0-99).

   This intrinsic is not recommended, due to the fact that its return
value for year wraps around century boundaries (change from a larger
value to a smaller one).  Therefore, programs making use of this
intrinsic, for instance, might not be Year 2000 (Y2K) compliant.  For
example, the date might appear, to such programs, to wrap around as of
the Year 2000.

   See @{"IDate Intrinsic (UNIX)" link "IDate Intrinsic (UNIX)"}, for information on obtaining more digits
for the current date.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"IDate Intrinsic (UNIX)" link "IDate Intrinsic (UNIX)"}.

@endnode

