@node "Kill Intrinsic (function)" "g77.guide/Kill Intrinsic (function)"
@next "Link Intrinsic (function)"
@prev "JZExt Intrinsic"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

Kill Intrinsic (function)
.........................

     Kill(PID, SIGNAL)

Kill: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

PID: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

SIGNAL: @{b}INTEGER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}badu77@{ub}.

Description:

   Sends the signal specified by SIGNAL to the process PID.  Returns 0
on success or a nonzero error code.  See @{b}kill(2)@{ub}.

   Due to the side effects performed by this intrinsic, the function
form is not recommended.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"Kill Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "Kill Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

@node "Link Intrinsic (function)" "g77.guide/Link Intrinsic (function)"
@next "QAbs Intrinsic"
@prev "Kill Intrinsic (function)"
@toc "Other Intrinsics"

Link Intrinsic (function)
.........................

     Link(PATH1, PATH2)

Link: @{b}INTEGER(KIND=1)@{ub} function.

PATH1: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

PATH2: @{b}CHARACTER@{ub}; scalar; INTENT(IN).

Intrinsic groups: @{b}badu77@{ub}.

Description:

   Makes a (hard) link from file PATH1 to PATH2.  A null character
(@{b}CHAR(0)@{ub}) marks the end of the names in PATH1 and PATH2--otherwise,
trailing blanks in PATH1 and PATH2 are ignored.  Returns 0 on success
or a nonzero error code.  See @{b}link(2)@{ub}.

   Due to the side effects performed by this intrinsic, the function
form is not recommended.

   For information on other intrinsics with the same name: See
@{"Link Intrinsic (subroutine)" link "Link Intrinsic (subroutine)"}.

@endnode

